column9: Lifetime: The number of people who had your Page's post enter their screen. Posts include statuses, photos, links, videos and more. (Unique Users)
column10: Lifetime: The number of people who had your Page's post enter their screen through unpaid distribution. (Unique Users)
column11: Lifetime: The number of people who had your Page's post enter their screen through paid distribution such as an ad. (Unique Users)
column12: Lifetime: The number of times your Page's post entered a person's screen. Posts include statuses, photos, links, videos and more. (Total Count)
column13: Lifetime: The number of times your Page's posts entered a person's screen through unpaid distribution. (Total Count)
column14: Lifetime: The number of times your Page's post entered a person's screen through paid distribution such as an ad. (Total Count)
column15: Lifetime: The number of unique people who engaged in certain ways with your Page post, for example by commenting on, liking, sharing, or clicking upon particular elements of the post. (Unique Users)
column16: Lifetime: The number of people who matched the audience targeting that clicked anywhere in your post on News Feed. (Unique Users)
column17: Lifetime: The number of clicks anywhere in your post on News Feed from the user that matched the audience targeting on it. (Total Count)
column18: Lifetime: The number of people who have given negative feedback to your post. (Unique Users)
column19: Lifetime: The number of times people have given negative feedback to your post. (Total Count)
column20: Lifetime: The number of impressions of your Page post to people who have liked your Page. (Total Count)

column24: Lifetime: The number of people who have liked your Page and clicked anywhere in your posts. (Unique Users)

column3:
MEET THE QUEENS: 

Queen Saya Naomi is an ORIGINAL Drag Queen artist whose presence is best known for her unique and fresh performances in New York and Chicago. 

Saya Naomi holds true drag queen badness in her tiny fist, with one of the freshest, fishiest looks around today. Saya Naomi - the “Bad Girl of Halsted” - has arrived and is fiercer than ever, slaying the stages with the hottest jams and putting Beyoncé’s weave to shame.

She'll be serving lqqks and cake tomorrow at SLAY x OTV present Two Queens in a Kitchen (LIVE) with Mister Wallace. Tune in at 8pm CST for this whole ass snack www.2QIK.live or buy a ticket to be a part of the live studio audience at Reunion Chicago: https://bit.ly/2yQLuVX

We've added 5 more tickets to SLAY x OTV present Two Queens in a Kitchen (LIVE) for a few of you lucky QTs. Come and get your life as we welcome our dear friend and OTV writer, Ashley Ray to the set of #2QIK this Saturday. Ray is a Chicago-based comic, writer and storyteller. Her work has been featured in The A.V. Club, Vice, Jezebel, The Chicago Reader and most recently in OTV - Open Television's #HairStory.

As a comic and storyteller, she has performed at
Helltrap Nightmare, Clickhole Live, the Best Night Ever showcase, You're Being Ridiculous, The Laugh Factory, iO, and the Steppenwolf Theatre. She has been featured as a guest on a number of podcasts and radio shows. In 2017, The Chicago Reader voted Ashley the 2nd Best Chicagoan to Follow on Twitter. Get dem tickets: https://bit.ly/2yQLuVX or tune in live at www.2qik.live.

It's the Monday after #pride weekend, you're tired, maybe a bit hungover, and looking for something to binge watch. Don't worry we gotchu. The first 11 episodes of Brujos are available to stream created by artist, writer, academic, The Hoodoisie creator, and Two Queens in a Kitchen Season 1 alum, Ricardo Gamboa. 

Donate to help them finish the finale: https://bit.ly/2IrHwmc

BRUJOS is a supernatural series about gay, Latino doctoral students who are also witches trying to survive the semester and a witch hunt led by a secret society of the straight, wealthy, white male descendants of the first New World colonizers.

Brujos is directed by Gamboa and Reshmi Hazra Rustebakke, executive produced by Cinema Libertad in association with Full Spectrum Features. It's produced by Olivia Curry and Adela and Pedro Gamboa. Directors of Photography: Zoe Lubeck and Zapata. 

#Brujostv stars Gamboa, Justin Ignatius Mitchell, Isaac Gomez, Jake Szczepaniak, and many more. 

#OTVRewind #2QIK

RSVP to join the studio audience of Two Queens in a Kitchen (LIVE) at Reunion this Saturday: https://bit.ly/2JQ85pU

#TheDarlingSeries is a docu-series by Diana Quinones Rivera that follows choreographer and #2QIK season 1 alum Darling Shear and her group of dancers as they explore their personal understandings of identity, expression, movement, and collaboration.

Keep your ear to the ground, the series premieres next month. 

See if this season's queens cast spells as tasty as Darling's and RSVP to be a part of our LIVE studio audience:  https://bit.ly/2JQ85pU

Kiam Marcelo Junio is a holistic healer and interdisciplinary artist creating work across media through dance and performance, video, installation, photography, and writing. They are also one of the stars of Two Queens in a Kitchen season 1! 

Kiam is the creator of BLOOM, a new self care potion. They were inspired to make BLOOM when they realized how much societal shame they’ve inherited about the butt. Contemporary culture values the butt as an aesthetic object and hardly as an integral part of the body that deserves love and care. Junio wants to help change that. BLOOM is crafted with all-natural botanicals, working with nature’s inherent healing intelligence. DM Kiam Marcelo Junio if you’d like a bottle! [1oz $10, 2oz $15, 4oz $25 ] ( Booth photos by @adrianlordz )

Get your snaps and claps ready for Two Queens in a Kitchen (LIVE) at Reunion coming at you June 30th, RSVP link: https://bit.ly/2JQ85pU

#OTVrewind #2QIK

Congratulation to Daniel Kyri Madison, co-creator of #TheTTV, for being recognized in this year's Windy City Times 30 under 30!

Kyri, alongside co-creator Bea Cordelia Sullivan-Knoff, have truly created a masterpiece in the T - Web Series, which premiered on Monday. 

The #TheTTV, Jo, a trans woman craving an increasingly elusive intimacy, and Carter, a queer Black man at odds with his conservative upbringing, converge from opposite sides of Chicago for a magical New Year's Eve night.

Watch #TheTTV now: http://www.weareo.tv/originals/the-t

Sur La Nuit is a soliloquy to the night, reflecting on love, loss, and identity. Presented thru the lens of otherness – queer identity, race, familial dynamics, gender, and access into classical art forms.

#SurLaNuit is composed by and stars ALEXA GRÆ, the piece is co-created by Jon Wes as videographer and Matthew Ozawa as director.

Watch it here or at http://www.weareo.tv/presents/sur-la-nuit

#pride #blackpride

If you've picked up a Chicago publication in the last week you've probably seen cultural producer and resident party mom Kristen Kaza in it. You can learn about her queer root in the Chicago Reader: https://bit.ly/2MLoxqi or check out her interview in Time Out Chicago with LGBT hall-of-famer Pat McCombs: https://bit.ly/2Lxw4rj

Well, this cornerstone of Chicago queer programming and star of Two Queens in a Kitchen season 2 has the #pride blowout to end all blowouts coming up on June 23rd! It's lovingly called #QueerthePier/ Navy Pier Pride presented by American Airlines. The femme future will be in full effect.  

Two Queens in a Kitchen (LIVE) at Reunion (a gallery co-managed by Kaza) is coming at you 6/30 complete with a LIVE feed so you can join the party wherever you are. If you're in Chicago, join our studio audience: https://bit.ly/2JQ85pU

In 2017, Derrick Woods-Morrow (one of this year's Windy City Times 30 under 30 recipients!) returned home to Greensboro, NC to reconnect with a police officer, who was once just another feral young boy on the playgrounds much like himself. Throughout a 72-hour period, they return to past moments of play, in an attempt to build a future were they could be like they once were – two young boys, searching for each other, deep into the bushes, one white & one unaware of his blackness,  Woods-Morrow knowing his body and mind could never truly return to that past.

The Roach is Coming will be on OTV for A LIMITED TIME ONLY until August 1. So watch it NOW! 

Watch #TheRoachisComing right here or at http://www.weareo.tv/presents/the-roach-is-coming

https://vimeo.com/275901309 

#pride #blackpride

Everyone has a hair story. We change our hair after a break-up, for a job, before balding, or to prep for a big event. Very few TV series focus on hair! Hair Story follows residents of a Chicago co-op as they try to get along and as they narrate wild dreams and stories to Gia, the hair stylist of the house. Hearing their stories inspires her to break her hiatus and return to her first love, the art of drag and gender transformation! 

Watch Hair Story now, right here or on #OTV: http://www.weareo.tv/presents//hair-story

Directed by Aymar Jean Christian, written by Roger Fierro, Felicia Holman, Abra Johnson, Philly Bigx Philly, Niki Madison, Eli Micky, Meida Teresa McNeal, Saya Naomi, Jordy Palmer, Ashley Ray, Erik Lamar Wallace II.

On the heels of #Juneteenth, check out these three blackity-black film pieces that redefine #BlackPride, now streaming on #OTV.  

1: "Hair Story" by Aymar Jean Christian, Felicia Holman, Roger Fierro, Abra Johnson, Phillip Lambert, Jr., Niki Madison, Eli Micky, Meida Teresa McNeal, Saya Naomi, Jordy Palmer, Ashley Ray, and Erik Lamar Wallace II. Residents of an artsy Black co-op tell their wild stories to an out-of-work drag queen as she styles their hair to pay her rent.

2: "Sur La Nuit" by ALEXA GRÆ, Jon Wes, and Matthew Ozawa. A soliloquy to the night, reflecting on love, loss, and identity.

3: "The Roach Is Coming" by Derrick Woods-Morrow. A reflection on the artist's racially charged upbringing in North Carolina. 

#pridemonth #pride

We're diving back into #OTVrewind visiting the queens of #2QIK past and seeing what their beat is these days. 

Rapbrarian (rapper + librarian) Roy Kinsey is a Chicago native whose 11-track album "Blackie: A Story by Roy Kinsey" was released this spring. The album tells a cohesive story focused on the Great Migration beginning with his grandmother's birth in Mississippi in 1943. A fitting soundtrack to celebrate your #Juneteenth. 

He was also one of the stars of Two Queens in a Kitchen in its very first season, alongside MSMRJR, speaking on political demonstrations vs. protests and creating access to the resources that people need while making a shaved asparagus salad and guacamole. 

Watch his episode here: https://bit.ly/2taBmlD.

Join our studio audience at the LIVE taping of Two Queens in a Kitchen (LIVE) at Reunion happening Saturday June 30th. RSVP link in event.

“As a trans woman myself, and for Daniel Kyri Madison as a queer black man, we’re all too acquainted with the stories people tell about us that are tragic and reductive and that often come as a punchline to someone else’s story,” Bea Cordelia Sullivan-Knoff told The Daily Beast “We wanted to create something that was more sincere to our experiences.”

the T - Web Series is now LIVE and available to stream, watch the entire first season now: http://www.weareo.tv/originals/the-t

#TheTTV #TeamT

If you couldn't gather your edges fast enough to RSVP to the T World Premiere, never fear, we've got more queer as fuck programming for you. 

Finish #pridemonth right and be a part of our studio audience for the LIVE taping of Two Queens in a Kitchen season 3! RSVP: https://bit.ly/2JQ85pU

The day has finally come! 

the T World Premiere rolls this evening at Chicago Cultural Center.  Doors are at 6pm (registration is sold out so come on time!) Screening starts at 7pm. Although it's sold out, there is a waitlist that we highly recommend signing up for. https://bit.ly/2MA03jq

Then slide through to the after party at Broken Shaker at Freehand Chicago starting at 9pm with performances by Ariel Zetina and Growing Concerns Poetry Collective. No RSVP required for the after party.
See McKenzie Chinn perform at the T World Premiere on Monday!

Today we’re checking in on the queens of seasons past to peep their current slay. 

First up is Coriama whose docu-web series, Queer The Air, came out this past fall.  The show is centered around interviews with black queer folx and covers everything from gender identity and relationships to body image and self-care. 

You can watch the pilot on our Vimeo vimeo.com/opentelevision, season one features comic and writer Ashley Ray and Keon Dillon of http://millennialsoulfood.com/. Watch the pilot here: https://vimeo.com/244731429

Two Queens in a Kitchen (LIVE) at Reunion is coming for you June 30th! Check out the Facebook event for more info on our LIVE taping of season 3 and join our studio audience.
OTV - Open Television

Mark your calendars for the LIVE filming of Two Queens in a Kitchen season three! #2QIK

Be a part of the magic at Reunion Chicago on Saturday June 30th. If you're not in Chicago, the entire event will be livestreamed in partnership with Mainstream Media, LLC so be sure to tune in! More details and livestream link to come.

The countdown begins! 

SEVEN short days away from this groundbreaking event - the premiere of #TheTTV, a dramedy following Jo and Carter, a young trans woman and queer Black man, as they learn how to be best friends in the wake of their romantic relationship and Jo's transition.

Make sure to RSVP! Eventbrite: https://bit.ly/2sz0vX2

SEEN by ALEXA GRÆ has arrived! Dive into this incredibly rich masterpiece and join us this evening to experience the visual counterpart to Sur La Nuit at Open Television Premieres: New Black TV. 

Program begins at 7:30pm at Black Cinema House.
OTV - Open Television

Thank you AFROPUNK for this feature of Sex Is A God Thing - The Webseries! 

Production of this sexy, powerful series from Rashida KhanBey Miller begins next month. Help them bring the project to life and support them and learn more on their Seed&Spark page: https://www.seedandspark.com/fund/sexisagodthing#story

Sur La Nuit is a soliloquy to the night, reflecting on love, loss, and identity. The short film, composed by ALEXA GRÆ, is presented thru the lens of otherness - queer identity, race, familial dynamics, gender, and access into classical art forms. Submerge yourself in all of this delicious darkness this Friday at Open Television Premieres: New Black TV at Black Cinema House.
